===Etymology===
From {{inh-lite|zh|sit-pro|*(g/k)uŋ||hole; orifice; inner part}}. {{och-l|孔|gloss=hole}} is probably the endoactive derivation of {{och-l|空|id=1|gloss=hollow; empty}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Cognate with {{cog|bo|ཁུང||hole}}, {{cog-lite|kac|ladi hku|ladi '''hku'''|nostril}}, {{cog|cdm|घाङ्‌|tr=gʰaŋ|t=hole}}, {{cog|my|ခေါင်း||cavity}}, {{cog|nxq|ko³³||cave; hole; pit}} (STEDT). See also {{och-l|坑|pit}} and {{och-l|肛|anus}}, which may or may not be related.

